Title : Gornje Hrasno
Text : [[File:Hrasno (Neum).jpg|thumb|Gornje Hrasno village.]]
'''Gornje Hrasno''' ({{lang-sr-cyr|Горње Храсно}}) is a settlement in the [[Neum]] municipality, in [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]. According to the 1991 census, it had a total of 186 inhabitants, out of which 108 were [[Serbs]] (58,06%); 73 were [[Croats]] (39,25%) and 5 were [[Muslims by ethnicity|Muslims]] (2,69%). It was the only settlement in Neum with a Serb majority.

